This expression transformation evaluates the value of the "Update Flag", a port which is used to take actions (like Insert/Update) downstream in the mapping. The possible values that an Update Flag may take are (I = Insert new record), (B = Insert new record and mark for soft delete), (U = Update existing record), (D = Update existing record and mark for soft delete) and (X = Reject). For more information on the evaluation logic, please see the description of the port "UPDATE_FLG".
For existing records, a given set of columns are compared to decide whether or not to update the record. If you wish to add more columns to this list, you can extend the comparison (which happens in a variable port called "SYSTEMS_COLS_DIFF").

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
The update flag is evaluated using logic, the English description of which is as follows:
Basic Checks: If the current ETL Process Identifier is same as target record's ETL Process Identifier, then it is already loaded and hence no processing required (result X for Reject) - STOP. If stage reject flag = Y, then no processing (result X for Reject) - STOP.
Checks for new records (where target's ETL Process Identifier is NULL) : If stage delete flag = Y, then insert record and mark it for soft-delete (result B for insert with soft-delete) - STOP. If stage delete flag <> Y, insert into target (result I for Insert) - STOP.
Checks for existing records (where target's ETL Process Identifier is NOT NULL) : If INSERT_ONLY_FLG = Y, then no processing (result X for Reject) - STOP. If stage delete flag = Y and target delete flag = Y then no processing (result X for Reject) - STOP. If stage delete flag = Y and target delete flag <> Y then update target and mark for soft-delete (result D for Updates with soft-delete) - STOP. If stage delete flag <> Y, update the target if there is difference in comparison columns (result U for Update) - STOP. If there is no difference in comparison columns, then no processing (result X for Reject) - STOP.
TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF(LKP_ETL_PROC_WID = ETL_PROC_WID, 'X', IIF(REJECT_FLG = 'Y','X', IIF(ISNULL(LKP_ETL_PROC_WID), IIF(DELETE_FLG = 'Y','B','I'), IIF(INSERT_ONLY_FLG = 'Y', 'X', IIF(DELETE_FLG = 'Y', IIF(LKP_DELETE_FLG = 'Y', 'X', 'D'), IIF(SYSTEMS_COLS_DIFF = 'Y', 'U','X'))))))

The SQL statement of this lookup transformation is overridden with a join with the staging area table to minimize the number of records to be cached by this lookup.
INSTANCE.NAME: Lkp_W_GL_REVN_F

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION:
This expression transformation evaluates the value of the "Update Flag", a port which is used to take actions (like Insert/Update) downstream in the mapping. The possible values that an Update Flag may take are (I = Insert new record), (B = Insert new record and mark for soft delete), (U = Update existing record), (D = Update existing record and mark for soft delete) and (X = Reject). For more information on the evaluation logic, please see the description of the port "UPDATE_FLG".
For existing records, a given set of columns are compared to decide whether or not to update the record. If you wish to add more columns to this list, you can extend the comparison (which happens in a variable port called "SYSTEMS_COLS_DIFF").
However, for this to work, you should also extend the previous lookup transformation to output your requested columns from the target table.
INSTANCE.NAME: Exp_W_GL_REVN_F_Update_Flg

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This Update Strategy transformation is the place where actions are taken based on the value of the Update Flag, whether to Insert or Update the record into the datawarehouse. If the Update Flag is (I or B), records are inserted. If it is (U or D), records are updated. For all other values, records are rejected.
INSTANCE.NAME: Upd_W_GL_REVN_F_Ins_Upd

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This filter transformation filters out records that have an UPDATE_FLG value of 'X'.
INSTANCE.NAME: Fil_W_GL_REVN_F

INSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This expression transformation helps in customizing this mapping. If you are adding new columns to this mapping and you have special logic/treatment for your own columns, this expression transformation box acts as a placeholder for all your transformations. For example, if you are adding three new columns, you should pull them all the way from the Source Qualifier to the Filter directly (unless you need them for comparing as well, in which case you have to take them through the update flag transformation box as well). From the Filter, your columns go inside this custom transformation box where you can play around with these. After you're done, take the output ports straight to the Update strategy transformation, and from there, to the target.
INSTANCE.NAME: Exp_Custom

METADATAEXTENSION.DESCRIPTION: The target data model version that this mapping is designed to load
